                                         CAPE TOWN - Mitchells Plain police have arrested two men for being in possession of a firearm, ammunition and 18 units of heroin. Members attached to anti-gang unit, Operation Combat, apprehended the men while patrolling the area on Monday night. Officers then received a tip-off about an illegal firearm buried on an open field in Morgenster Road. A further search of the area resulted in the discovery of a hunting rifle with four rounds of ammunition.